HEADWORD: Cross-garnet
<hw>Cross"-gar`net</hw> <pr>(kr?s"g?r`n?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
hinge having one strap perpendicular and the other strap horizontal
giving it the form of an Egyptian or T cross.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossgrained</ent>⟦br⟧
